<subSubSection pageId="190" pageNumber="191" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="190.[151,457,404,430]" box="[151,457,404,430]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,457,404,430]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,457,404,430]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[207,345,404,430]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Ratcheuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,345,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">Ratcheuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="190.[151,1437,474,679]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">
This complex includes only the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch, 1985" authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1985" box="[727,1051,474,499]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Ratcheuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[727,853,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">Ratcheuma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch" box="[862,1051,474,499]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1985) Two new genera of cave-dwelling millipedes (Diplopoda), with remarks on the millipede fauna of West Caucasian caves. International Journal of Speleology, 14, 39 - 50. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5038 / 1827 - 806 X. 14.1.5" type="journal article" year="1985">Golovatch, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 31 body segments in adults (including telson). This is the only genus amongst the Caucasian Anthroelucosomatidae which is characterized by the complete absence of telopodites on the posterior gonopods, a feature shared with some Balkan forms. The genus was placed within the 
<taxonomicName box="[506,651,583,606]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Caucaseuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,651,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">Caucaseuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex by 
<bibRefCitation box="[816,1055,582,607]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" refString="Curcic, B. P. M., Makarov, S. E., Tomic, V. T., Mitic, B. M., Curcic, S. B., Dudic, B. D., Lucic, L. R. &amp; Jasnic, N. (2008) On a new genus of endemic millipedes (Diplopoda: Chordeumatida: Anthroleucosomatidae) from the Balkan Peninsula. Zootaxa, 1743, 1 - 16." type="journal article">
Ćurčić 
<emphasis box="[904,960,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
together with 
<taxonomicName box="[1237,1382,583,606]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Caucaseuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1237,1382,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">Caucaseuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,297,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">
<taxonomicName box="[151,293,618,643]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Adshardicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Adshardicus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but the absence of telopodites on the posterior gonopods clearly separates this genus from all other Caucasian anthroleucosomatid complexes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
